-- An nr function for Linear-or-affine.
--
-- The value of nrВ pВ рқҹҳВ zВ sВ n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If pВ =В рқҹҷ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls, and the
--   argument is used exactly once in the successor case (excluding
--   erased uses):
--
--     f zero    = f_z
--     f (suc m) = f_s m
--
--   Let us use nВ +В z for the zero case, and nВ +В s for the successor
--   case: the result is a conservative approximation of these two
--   values (their meet).
--
-- * If pВ =В рқҹҳ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive
--   calls, and the argument is not used (in non-erased positions) in
--   the successor case:
--
--     f zero    = f_z
--     f (suc m) = f_s
--
--   Let us again use nВ +В z for the zero case. For the successor case
--   we use вүӨрқҹҷВ В·В nВ +В s: the argument is not used linearly in the
--   successor case, because it is not used at all, so if n is рқҹҷ, then
--   the result should be at most вүӨрқҹҷ (not рқҹҷ, because the function is
--   not linear, and not рқҹҳ, because that would amount to an erased
--   match on a natural number).
--
-- * If pВ =В вүӨрқҹҷ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls, and
--   the argument is used at most once in the successor case
--   (excluding erased uses). Let us again use nВ +В z for the zero
--   case, and вүӨрқҹҷВ В·В nВ +В s for the successor case.
--
-- * If pВ =В вүӨПү, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls. In the
--   successor case the argument is used an unlimited number of times,
--   so we use вүӨПүВ В·В nВ +В s. In the zero case we use nВ +В z, as before.
--
-- All of these cases can be expressed in the following way (note that
-- рқҹҷВ вҲ§В рқҹҳ and рқҹҷВ вҲ§В вүӨрқҹҷ are both equal to вүӨрқҹҷ):
--
--   nr p рқҹҳ z s n = ((рқҹҷ вҲ§ p) В· n + s) вҲ§ (n + z)
--
-- The value of nrВ pВ рқҹҷВ zВ sВ n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If pВ =В рқҹҳ, then we have linear recursion: the argument is used
--   linearly (n), the successor case can occur an unlimited number of
--   times (вүӨПүВ В·В s), and the zero case occurs once (z).
--
-- * If p is рқҹҷ, вүӨрқҹҷ orВ вүӨПү, then there is recursion (вүӨПүВ В·В s), the
--   argument can be used in each recursive call (вүӨПүВ В·В n), and the
--   zero case occurs once (z).
--
-- We get the following definition:
--
--   nr p рқҹҷ z s n = (рқҹҷ + p) В· n + вүӨПү В· s + z
--
-- The value of nrВ pВ вүӨрқҹҷВ zВ sВ n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If pВ =В рқҹҳ, then we have affine recursion: the argument is used
--   affinely (вүӨрқҹҷВ В·В n), the successor case can occur an unlimited
--   number of times (вүӨПүВ В·В s), and the zero case occurs at most once
--   (вүӨрқҹҷВ В·В z).
--
-- * If p is рқҹҷ, вүӨрқҹҷ orВ вүӨПү, then there is recursion (вүӨПүВ В·В s), the
--   argument can be used in each recursive call (вүӨПүВ В·В n), and the
--   zero case occurs at most once (вүӨрқҹҷВ В·В z).
--
-- We get the following definition:
--
--   nr p рқҹҷ z s n = (вүӨрқҹҷ + p) В· n + вүӨПү В· s + вүӨрқҹҷ В· z
--
-- Finally we use the following definition for nrВ pВ вүӨПүВ zВ sВ n:
--
--   nr _ вүӨПү z s n = вүӨПү В· (n + s + z)
--
-- There is recursion (вүӨПүВ В·В s), in the successor case there can be
-- multiple recursive calls (вүӨПүВ В·В n), and the zero case can occur
-- multiple times (вүӨПүВ В·В z).

